{[%evp 0,90,17,13,43,43,52,47,77,50,60,72,56,79,96,84,61,56,64,48,44,40,37,38,
52,47,23,23,22,16,12,24,39,37,35,12,31,22,10,17,16,15,10,-5,-9,-10,-3,-5,-5,
-23,-25,-18,-20,-29,-26,-63,-45,-53,-45,-57,-30,-27,-25,-27,-27,-23,-15,-12,
-23,-23,-21,-27,-27,-22,-22,-22,-22,-29,-30,-50,-55,-49,-47,-69,-64,-88,-88,
-109,-104,-104,-106,-107,-114] A common type of endgame that occurs in the
Scandinavian: White has the bishop pair but weaknesses on the kingside} 1. e4
d5 (1... c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Nd7 5. c3 Ngf6 6. Nxf6+ Nxf6 7. Nf3
Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 e6 (9... Qd5 10. Qg3) 10. Bc4 $14 {is the best move
because it prevents a trade of queens and keeps the bishop pair} (10. Bd3 Qd5
11. Qxd5 {White is very slightly better but Black has a clear plan and easily
holds} Nxd5 (11... cxd5) 12. O-O Be7 13. Bd2 O-O 14. Rad1 Rad8 15. Be4 Rd7 $11
{[%cal Yf8d8] Black is a tad worse but his position is stable enough. A c5
break might be possible in the future})) 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qd6 4. d4 Nf6 5.
Nf3 Bg4 6. h3 Bh5 7. g4 Bg6 8. Ne5 Nbd7 9. Nxg6 hxg6 10. Qf3 c6 11. Be3 Nb6 12.
O-O-O Nbd5 13. Nxd5 Qxd5 14. Qxd5 Nxd5 {With queens on the board, such a
position tends to be better for White. However with the queens off, Black is a
happy camper} (14... cxd5 $5 {is a good alternative} 15. Bb5+ Kd8 16. f3 e6 17.
c3 Ne8 18. Bd3 Rc8 19. Kd2 Nd6 $11) 15. Bd2 b5 {Securing the d5 square for the
knight} (15... e6 {is too slow. White will gain a lot of space after c4, g5
and crash through with d5} 16. c4 (16. Bg2 Bd6 17. Kb1 b5 (17... O-O-O 18. c4
Nf4)) 16... Nf6 17. Bg2 Be7 18. g5 Nd7 19. d5 $16) 16. c3 e6 17. b3 Rb8 {
Prophylaxis against c4: if that happens Rb8 would be ideally placed} 18. Kc2
Kd7 19. Bg2 Bd6 (19... Be7 20. Rhe1 a5 $132 {Black's position is more than fine
}) 20. Ra1 a5 21. a4 $2 (21. h4 $14) 21... b4 $15 22. c4 Nf4 23. Bxf4 Bxf4 24.
Rad1 g5 25. Kd3 Kc7 26. Ke2 Rbd8 27. Rd3 Rd7 28. Rhd1 Rhd8 29. Bf1 e5 30. dxe5
Rxd3 31. Rxd3 Re8 32. Kf3 Rxe5 33. Rd1 Re6 34. Bd3 Bd6 35. Bf5 Re7 36. Be4 Bc5
37. Rd2 g6 38. Bc2 Re1 39. Rd1 Rxd1 40. Bxd1 Kd6 41. Ke4 Bxf2 42. c5+ Ke6 43.
Be2 f5+ 44. Kf3 Bxc5 45. Bc4+ Kf6 1/2-1/2

