-76,-112,-107,-134,-139,-472] White played unambitiously and Black got
everything he could possibly want from the opening} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3.
Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Bc4 e6 7. O-O Bb4 $1 {Developing with a tempo
in order to castle fast!} 8. Bb3 Nbd7 9. Ne2 O-O (9... O-O-O $6 {is a good
option too. Black has the choice to go for either short or long castling but I
think this is not necessary here}) 10. Ng3 Bg6 11. Qe2 Rfe8 12. Nh4 Rad8 13.
Nxg6 hxg6 14. Rd1 c6 {In such positions it is not critical if the computer
gives a small plus for White or Black: the game is unclear and both players
have chances. I find Black's play easier} 15. Bf4 Nd5 16. Bg5 N5f6 17. Bf4 Be7
18. Nf1 Nh5 19. Bd2 Qc7 20. Qf3 Bd6 21. h3 Ndf6 22. Bg5 Rd7 23. c3 Nh7 24. Be3
