-41,-48,-46,-32,-35,-28,-34,-42,0,-4,-17,-14,-16,-11,-7,-12,-15,-16,-26,-32,0,
-22,0,0,0,0,0] Another game that explores the often resulting positions
without light-squared bishops. The most critical factor here is piece activity
} 1. e4 $1 d5 $1 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Ne5 c6 7. Bd3
Bxd3 8. Qxd3 Qa6 $6 {During the game, I thought I was being clever with this
move but in fact, it is a dubious decision} (8... Nbd7 9. Nxd7 {good move
forcing Black's knight away from the center} Nxd7 10. O-O Nf6 11. Bd2 (11. Ne4
Nxe4 12. Qxe4 e6 13. c4 Be7 14. Bf4 (14. Be3 O-O 15. Rfd1 Rad8 (15... Bf6) 16.
h3 Rd7 17. a3 Rfd8 18. Rd2 Bf6 (18... Qa4) 19. Rad1 Qa4 $17) 14... O-O 15. Rfd1
Bf6 {Black managed to develop and has an equal game} (15... Rfd8 16. Be5 Rd7)
16. Be5 Bxe5 17. dxe5 Qb4 18. b3 Rad8 19. h3 a5 $11) 11... e6 12. Ne4 Qh5 $132
13. Rfe1 Be7 14. Qb3 O-O-O $11) 9. Qf3 Nbd7 10. Bf4 e6 11. O-O-O {White is
more active and as a result is slightly better} Be7 (11... Bb4 {is worth
considering too} 12. Nxd7 Nxd7 13. d5 $2 (13. Kb1 Bxc3 14. Qxc3 O-O 15. Qg3 $14
) 13... cxd5 14. Nxd5 exd5 15. Rxd5 O-O $19) 12. Nxd7 Nxd7 13. Qg3 Nf6 $5 14.
Qxg7 Rg8 15. Qh6 b5 16. a3 Rg6 (16... b4 $1 17. axb4 Qa1+ 18. Nb1 (18. Kd2 Qxb2
19. Rb1 Ne4+ 20. Nxe4 Qxd4+ 21. Kc1 Qxe4 $17) 18... a5 $17) 17. Qh3 b4 18. axb4
Bxb4 19. Kb1 Bxc3 20. Qxc3 Nd5 21. Qf3 Rf6 22. g3 Rb8 23. Qd3 (23. Rd3 Rb4 $15)
(23. Rhe1 $5 Rb4 24. b3 Qb6 $13) 23... Qxd3 24. Rxd3 Nxf4 25. gxf4 Rxf4 26. Rg1
Ke7 $6 (26... Rb5 $15 27. f3 Rh5 28. Rg2 a5 $15) 27. f3 Rb5 28. Rg4 Rf6 29. Rh4
h6 30. f4 a5 31. Kc1 Rb4 32. c3 Rb5 33. Kc2 a4 34. Rdh3 Ra5 35. Re3 a3 36. bxa3
Rxa3 37. Kb2 Ra8 1/2-1/2

