transposed to a structure more typical for the French Defense where Black has
the nice c5 break at an opportune moment. The f3, Nge2 setup chosen by White
is way too passive and only results in weaknesses and lack of coordination} 1.
e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Bd2 Bg4 $1 6. f3 Bd7 $1 7. Bc4 Qb6
$1 8. Nge2 e6 9. O-O Be7 10. Kh1 O-O $11 11. Bb3 (11. Be3 c5 12. dxc5 Bxc5 13.
