Nxd5 14. Bxd5 Nc6 $15 (14... Bf6 $15)) 12... Qxc5 {The awkward combination of
f3, Ne2, Bb3 together with Black's great activity swing the evaluation in his
favor} 13. Ne4 (13. Qe1 Nc6 (13... Bc6) 14. Qg3 Bd6 15. Bf4 Bxf4 16. Nxf4 Rad8
17. Rad1 Bc8 {Black has nothing to be afraid of}) 13... Nxe4 14. fxe4 Nc6 15.
c3 Rad8 16. Qc1 Na5 17. Bc2 Nc4 18. Bf4 Bf6 19. Ng3 Be5 20. h3 Bxf4 21. Rxf4
