{[%evp 0,112,28,30,49,29,52,59,63,63,70,59,40,5,108,68,104,61,72,71,73,51,63,
28,34,8,13,-15,-15,-46,14,-19,5,9,26,-31,11,-8,8,1,-1,-36,-27,-36,-33,-28,-24,
-89,-92,-101,-67,-77,-81,-81,-19,-16,-11,-11,-12,-10,-12,-9,7,9,13,-14,-8,-44,
-35,-36,-22,-14,0,-8,-11,-56,-47,-85,-82,-89,-25,-19,-1,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,-261,
-287,-317,-363,-374,-400,-29995,-382,-414,-624,-741,-286,-317,-322,-339,-498,
-520,-229,-255,-127,-187,-254,-265,-283] The game transposed to a structure
resembling the French defense where later a well-timed c6-c5 break allowed
Black to come on top. The ensuing endgame has a couple of educational moments
too.} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Bd2 Bg4 6. f3 Bf5 7. Bc4
Qb6 8. Nge2 e6 9. O-O c6 10. Kh1 Be7 {White has played somewhat passively
whereas Black has made natural solid moves. Next, the second player will
finish up his development and unleash the c5 break at an appropriate moment}
11. Bb3 O-O 12. Be3 Nbd7 (12... Nd5 13. Bf2 Nd7 14. Ne4 $14) 13. Ng3 Bg6 14.
Nce4 Qc7 {escaping the potential discovered attack} 15. c3 c5 16. Qd2 (16. Nxc5
$6 Nxc5 17. dxc5 Bxc5 18. Bxc5 Qxc5 $17 {[%cal Yf6d5,Yd5e3] Black is better})
16... Rad8 17. Rad1 cxd4 18. cxd4 Nd5 19. Rc1 Qb6 20. Bf2 Bb4 21. Qd1 N7f6 22.
Nc5 Nf4 23. Ne2 Bxc5 24. Rxc5 Qxc5 25. dxc5 Rxd1 26. Bxd1 Bd3 27. Re1 Bxe2 28.
Bxe2 Nxe2 29. Rxe2 Rd8 {Black managed to achieve his strategic goal and get a
good knight vs bad bishop type of endgame. The next steps of the plan are to
infiltrate White's camp with the rook and put the knight on d5} 30. g3 Rd1+ 31.
Kg2 Nd5 32. a3 a5 33. Rc2 h5 $3 {A very important move gaining space} 34. f4 (
34. c6 bxc6 35. Rxc6 Rd2 $19 {[%cal Yd5e3]}) 34... Kh7 $17 35. Kf3 Rd3+ $6 36.
Ke2 Rb3 37. Be1 a4 {[%cal Yh7g6,Yg6f5]} 38. Bd2 Kg6 39. Bc1 Kf5 {The last
piece comes into the game} 40. Rc4 h4 41. Rxa4 hxg3 42. hxg3 Rxg3 43. Ra7 Ke4 {
Pressuring the opponent's king} 44. Rxb7 Rg2+ 45. Kf1 $4 Rc2 46. b4 Rxc1+ 47.
Kg2 Nxf4+ 48. Kg3 Rg1+ 49. Kf2 Rg2+ 50. Kf1 Rc2 51. Rxf7 Kf3 52. Ke1 Ke3 53.
Kd1 Rd2+ 54. Kc1 Ne2+ 55. Kb1 Nc3+ 56. Kc1 Ne2+ {I offered a draw since it was
enough for me in this Armaggedon game!} 1/2-1/2

