{[%evp 0,58,19,38,42,37,76,65,68,58,113,99,85,74,82,65,61,0,14,-11,-8,-3,-3,
-20,-21,-35,-39,-44,-20,-50,-52,-48,-38,-110,-113,-88,-93,-115,-115,-101,-101,
-95,-87,-80,-24,-22,-23,-23,-37,-32,-32,-83,-32,-79,-101,-105,-78,-129,-103,
-29989,-29990] The Scandinavian at its best! A demonstration that White should
know how to place his pieces and not just play random moves. In this game, he
played in a careless manner and rapidly got an inferior position} 1. e4 d5 2.
exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 c6 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. Bc4 Bf5 7. Bd2 e6 8. Ne5 Nbd7 9.
Nxd7 Nxd7 10. O-O Qb6 $1 11. Bc1 (11. Be3 Qxb2 $17) (11. Bb3 Qxd4 $17) 11...
Nf6 12. Bb3 Bd6 $15 13. Ne2 Qc7 $1 {[%cal Yd6h2] taking control of the
important diagonal} 14. h3 O-O-O $1 (14... O-O $1 $15 {is good enough for an
advantage too. However, once I saw 0-0-0 with a fast c6-c5 I could not help
but play it!}) 15. c3 c5 16. Bc2 Bxc2 17. Qxc2 cxd4 18. Qa4 (18. Nxd4 Bh2+ 19.
Kh1 Rxd4 $19 20. g3 Bxg3 21. fxg3 Rhd8 22. Bf4 Qc6+ $19) 18... d3 19. Nd4 a6
20. Rd1 e5 21. Nf5 g6 22. Bg5 gxf5 23. Bxf6 e4 24. Bxh8 Rxh8 25. b4 Qe7 26. b5
Qe5 27. Qc4+ Kb8 28. g3 Rg8 29. Qxf7 Rxg3+ 0-1

