{[%evp 0,36,35,9,35,42,63,63,62,69,48,52,54,39,34,-12,-6,-21,-14,-23,-10,-21,
-1,23,36,-27,-41,-108,-91,-89,-106,-147,-108,-105,-129,-207,-216,-224,-158]
Strong play and a great demonstration of positional knowledge by the French GM.
After the early trade of light-squared bishops, he immediately recognized the
opportunity to go for Nc6 and 0-0-0 taking over! The game shares very similar
ideas to the ones in Gonzalez Moreno-Cornette} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5
4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Bd3 Nc6 $3 7. Bxf5 Qxf5 8. Be3 O-O-O $3 {Black is
already better} 9. Qe2 e6 10. a3 g5 (10... Nd5 11. Nxd5 exd5 12. O-O-O Bd6 13.
Rhe1 Rhe8 (13... Na5) 14. Qd3 Ne7 15. Qxf5+ Nxf5 16. Bd2 f6 17. a4 h5 $17) 11.
O-O-O g4 12. Nh4 Qa5 13. Qb5 Qxb5 14. Nxb5 Nd5 15. c4 Nxe3 16. fxe3 Bh6 17. b3
Bxe3+ 18. Kc2 Bg5 0-1

