{[%evp 0,86,35,25,45,52,52,54,54,62,67,47,48,50,46,61,46,53,80,17,11,28,43,23,
20,33,20,17,35,15,-13,-7,19,-5,-7,-12,-16,-17,-23,-23,-5,-17,-27,-55,-17,-67,
-39,-87,-64,-76,-39,-44,-41,-61,-55,-57,-73,-74,-48,-67,-73,-80,-77,-84,-76,
-122,-90,-130,-90,-84,-93,-148,-121,-127,-127,-121,-112,-159,-95,-272,-318,
-353,-363,-367,-375,-376,-382,-384,-415] An example of the Qb5 topical idea} 1.
e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bd2 c6 8. Qe2 (
8. O-O Qc7 {with a very solid position} (8... Bb4 {is an alternative. Black's
position is very stable. Still, I do not see a reason to give up the bishop so
early and without need} 9. a3 Bxc3 10. Bxc3 Qc7 11. Ne5 Nbd7 12. Nxd7 Qxd7 13.
Re1 O-O 14. h3 Nd5 {[%cal Yc6d5,Yc4d5]} 15. Bd3 $6 {or another random move
will result in} Nxc3 $1 16. bxc3 Bxd3 $15 {where Black has an advantage due to
his opponent's broken structure})) 8... Bb4 9. O-O-O Nbd7 10. Kb1 Nb6 11. Bb3
Bxc3 12. Bxc3 Qb5 $3 {A magnificent idea that allows Black to get firm control
over the light squares!} 13. Qxb5 cxb5 $15 14. Ne5 a5 15. a3 Be4 $3 {A
critical move that shows a deep understanding of the position.Otherwise, the
bishop will be isolated with f3 and chased with g4, h4-h5: something Black
should always be careful about} (15... O-O $2 16. f3 Rfc8 (16... h5 $1 17. Rhg1
$132) 17. g4 Bg6 18. h4) 16. Rhe1 O-O 17. f3 Bd5 $15 18. Bxd5 Nfxd5 19. Bd2 Nc4
20. Bc1 (20. Nxc4 {results in an extremely passive position for White. White's
bishop is no match for the powerful Black knight} bxc4 21. c3 b5 (21... Rfe8)
22. Kc2 Rfe8 23. Ra1 a4 {not necessary here but a nice prophylaxis against an
a4 break} 24. Re2 f6 $15 {[%cal Yg8f7,Yg7g5,Yh7h5]}) 20... Rfc8 21. f4 b4 22.
Nxc4 Rxc4 23. Rd3 bxa3 24. Rxa3 b5 25. f5 b4 26. Rd3 exf5 27. Re5 Rd8 28. Rxf5
a4 29. Bd2 f6 $17 {[%cal Yg8f7] Black has a huge positional advantage and went
on to convert it} 30. h3 Kf7 31. g4 g6 32. Rff3 Re8 33. c3 Re2 34. cxb4 Nxb4
35. Rc3 Rxd4 36. Rc7+ Ke6 37. Bc1 Rd1 38. Rcc3 Red2 39. Rf4 Nd3 40. Rc6+ Kd5
41. Rfxf6 Rxb2+ 42. Ka1 Rb5 43. Rfd6+ Ke5 0-1

