{Another great example of the Qb5 strategy!} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5
4. d4 c6 5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Bd2 Nf6 7. Bc4 e6 8. Qe2 Bb4 9. a3 Bg4 10. O-O-O (10. h3
Bxc3 11. Bxc3 (11. hxg4 Bxd2+) 11... Qh5 $11) 10... Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Qh5 12. h3
Bxf3 13. gxf3 Nbd7 {Black has a fine game due to White's weaknesses on the
kingside} 14. Rhg1 Nb6 15. Bb3 O-O-O 16. Kb1 Rhg8 17. Rg3 Qb5 18. Qxb5 cxb5 19.
Ba5 Rd6 20. Bxb6 Rxb6 21. c3 Rd6 22. Re1 g6 23. Rg5 a6 24. Rge5 Kc7 25. Kc1 Kb6
26. Kd2 Rc8 27. R1e3 Nd7 28. Rg5 e5 29. Rd3 f6 30. Rg1 Rd8 31. Bc2 exd4 32.
cxd4 Nb8 33. Rg4 Nc6 34. Kc3 a5 35. b4 axb4+ 36. axb4 Ra8 37. Kb3 Ra4 38. Kc3
