we free our game with} c5 15. Nxd7 Qxd7 16. dxc5 Bxc5 {as we have already
mentioned in previous sessions, Black is better because we were very correct
to isolate his bishop on b3 to play a swift b5 move. There are often Qc6 ideas,
for example if} 17. Rf1 Qc6 {White can resign. It is a very typical tactic.
This clearly shows how strong Black's bishops and how weak White's bishops are.
}) 13... a6 ({Maybe even} 13... b4 {can be good. For example,} 14. Ne4 Nxe4 15.
Qxe4 c5)) {Even} 11... bxa4 $5 {is a very good idea.} 12. Bxa4 O-O {[%cal
