{[%evp 0,39,17,9,27,42,61,59,60,51,60,53,52,48,37,47,61,29,32,49,38,37,21,5,73,
19,40,41,42,17,127,134,124,50,126,314,408,488,982,1286,29999,-30000] Now we
will see a game that for me is a very painful memory. It is the only time in
my life that I lost in a miniature. It is important to not only learn from our
proud wins but also by our losses.} 1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nf3 Bg4 4. Be2 Nc6
5. O-O {This is an exciting setup.} ({He is way too good to play} 5. Nc3 {
This move, as we already mentioned, is inaccurate because of} Qd7 {and the d4
spot is now weak.}) 5... O-O-O {After I castled he played the cunning move} 6.
h3 {and now I went very wrong. This is an instructive game.} ({Again,} 6. Nc3 {
is not good because I will play} Qd7 {again, with a perfect game, for example,}
7. b4 {We already mentioned} e5 8. b5 Bxf3 9. Bxf3 Nd4 {with an at least equal
game for Black.}) 6... Bxf3 $2 {The move Bxf3 should be played only when d4
square is weak. In other words only when White's knight is already on c3 and
not on b1!} ({Both} 6... Bh5 $1 7. d3 (7. Nc3 {Let's say, I kind of lost a
tempo. But this tempo is the move h3 that is not so important.} Qd7 8. b4 Nf6
9. b5 Bxf3 10. Bxf3 Nd4 $15 {Same position as before only with the h3 move
which doesn't really matter.} 11. d3 Qf5 $3) 7... e6 8. Nc3 Qd7 9. Rb1 f5 $132)
({and especially} 6... Bf5 $5 {would have been better moves.} 7. Nc3 Qd7 8. Bb5
f6 9. d4 e6 10. Qe2 h5 $132 (10... Nge7 $132)) 7. Bxf3 Qd7 {What's the
difference with the previous games? The move Nc3 has not been played and it
will never be played. So here I thought I was doing very well and all of a
sudden he played} 8. c3 {this magnificent move, instead of Nc3. And now I
realized that, in fact, I am in trouble. I thought that after} e5 {I would
have a great game because of the backward pawns. But this is not the case.
Here, he is better.} (8... Ne5 {I believe that after} 9. d4 {again, White has
some advantage.} ({I don't know he was planning even} 9. Be2 {and} Nd3 {
Yes, but I am wasting too much energy.} 10. b4 {but maybe here, I am fine.
Most likely, he would have played 9.d4.})) 9. Re1 {Already, he has some
threats at some moment to take on c6, and I believe I played an excellent move
here but I am worse anyway.} Nf6 ({Maybe even} 9... f5 {would have been a good
move. Now he has to take the pawn.} 10. Bxc6 Qxc6 11. Rxe5 {That was my
intention to sacrifice the pawn and to gain some compensation. But the truth
is that there is not enough compensation.}) {He played a powerful move here:}
10. b4 {Playing d2, c3, and b4, it gives the impression that this is 
beginner's play. But, in fact, he knew exactly what he was doing. Take my word
for it; you cannot play c3 and b4, leaving the pawn on d2, unless you know
very well what to do.} ({Here, I think he was right not to take this pawn.} 10.
Bxc6 Qxc6 11. Rxe5 {We are not afraid to sacrifice this pawn because now I
have developed my knight.} Bd6 12. Re1 {Now, this is some kind of Benko Gambit
compensation, for example,} Rhe8 ({I can even play} 12... g5 {This is, in fact,
also an interesting move.} 13. d4 Rhg8 {[%cal Gg5g4] Intending to play a fast
g4 move. There seems to be some compensation here for Black. I wouldn't mind
playing at all playing this position with him.})) 10... Bd6 11. d3 {[%cal
Gd1a4,Gb1d2,Gd2e4,Gd1c4] In fact, here White has a very nice advantage. His
bishop on f3 is just way too strong. I was calculating moves but I would see
that the position was getting worse and worse.} Qf5 {I even gave him the
chance to take on c6.} 12. Qa4 {And, he didn't take on c6. I am much worse.}
Qxd3 ({Maybe, I should have played} 12... e4 {but, again, I am worse.} 13. dxe4
Qe5 14. g3 Bxb4) 13. b5 Nb8 14. Be3 {Very, very strong moves. He develops his
pieces and there is nothing I can do. The position is lost. Both his bishops
are pointing at my king. I thought for a lot of time, but this is beyond
salvation.} Qf5 ({If I play} 14... e4 {in fact, I am losing my queen.} 15. Rd1
{[%csl Rd3]}) 15. Nd2 {[%csl Gd2,Ge3] This is very instructive. Suddenly,
instead of taking the pawn, he developed all of his pieces.} Bc5 {This is
already dead lost. There is nothing I can do.} ({For example, if I go} 15... a6
{It is winning. He can take} 16. bxa6 ({I am sure, he can even take here} 16.
Bxb7+ Kxb7 17. bxa6+ {and give a checkmate very fast.})) 16. Ne4 {Very
powerful play.} Bxe3 ({If I take on e4} 16... Nxe4 {in fact, I am even losing
my queen.} 17. Bg4) 17. Rxe3 {I cannot play Nd5 because of Bg4.} h5 {It is too
late. He took finally} 18. Qxa7 {[%cal Ge4c5] threatening some ideas with Nc5}
Nd5 19. Nc5 {I thought for a long time but there was nothing I could do so
here I decided to allow checkmate.} Nxe3 20. Qxb7# 1-0

