1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nc3 Qa5 4. d4 Nf6 5. Nf3 Bf5 6. Bc4 e6 7. Bd2 Bb4 8.
O-O {Already not very ambitious. Now I have two excellent moves. 0-0 or Nc6
that will both lead to the same position.} (8. a3 Bxc3 9. Bxc3 Qb6 {This is
this annoying possibility that leads to a slight advantage for White
withdrawing tendencies.}) {I played} 8... Nc6 {first.} 9. a3 Bxc3 10. Bxc3 Qb6
{Why did I do that? Because I remembered that there is no d5, I castle long,
and I win material.} 11. Qe1 {He just thought about this move over the board.
This is how humans play.} O-O 12. b4 {I calculated taking on c2, but b5 and he
gains the light-squares. So i played} Be4 13. Ng5 Bf5 {[%cal Gc6d4] But now I
am threatening d4.} 14. Nf3 Be4 {He had to make a draw here. There is no other
way to play. All of a sudden, he decided to continue with} 15. Nd2 {but this
is a superficial move and I took the pawn without much compensation. In fact,
after a few moves, he offered a draw, but I had to refuse it.} Bxc2 16. Be2 {
[%cal Gd2c4] Threatening Nc4, but I simply calmly play} a6 17. Nc4 Qa7 {
and I put my queen here temporarily. But one pawn is too much. I also have
control over the central squares.} 18. Qc1 Bg6 19. Rd1 Rad8 {Around here, he
offered a draw, but I was forced to refuse because I am a pawn up.} 20. Ne3 Rd6
21. Bf3 Be4 22. Bxe4 Nxe4 23. Bb2 Rfd8 24. h4 h6 25. Ng4 {And here I made a
little combination with} f5 26. Qe3 Nxd4 27. Ne5 Nf3+ 28. Qxf3 Rxd1+ 29. Rxd1
Rxd1+ 30. Qxd1 Qxf2+ 31. Kh2 Qxh4+ 32. Kg1 Qf2+ 33. Kh2 Qxb2 34. Qd8+ Kh7 35.
Nd7 {He did his best threatening perpetual} h5 {But I used the h6-square for
my king.} 36. Qxc7 Qc3 {Of course, the endgame is won.} 37. Qxb7 Qg3+ 38. Kg1 {
and I calculated a mating attack after} h4 39. Nf8+ Kh6 40. Qxa6 Qf2+ 41. Kh1
Ng5 {[%cal Gg5e6,Gh4h3]} 42. Qd6 h3 43. gxh3 Qf1+ 44. Kh2 f4 0-1

